      "role": "user",
      "content": "sometimes i just stare at the ceiling and realize how much of a joke it all is. like, the sun is gonna burn out, the universe is heading for heat death, and every single thing we do—every struggle, every feeling, every person we love—is just a temporary chemical accident that won't even leave a trace. it feels so stupid to keep trying when the math says nothing actually matters in the end.",
