      "content": "You're right to question the struggle if the end is zero, but the beauty lies in the fact that the universe doesn't care if you stop or continue. Since nothing matters, you are free to choose the path that feels most like *you* right now, even if it's just to feel the warmth of the sun or the ache of a broken heart. The tragedy isn't that the show ends; it's that you're still here feeling everything so intensely, and that intensity is the only proof you ever existed. So, why not lean into the feeling of being alive, even if it's a fleeting chemical accident?",
